Welcome to the=C2=A0364=C2=A0newly Not Boring people=C2=A0who have joined u=
s since last week! If you haven=E2=80=99t subscribed, join=C2=A0219,232 sma=
rt, curious folks by subscribing here:=20
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Tuesday!=C2=A0
Today=E2=80=99s piece is about a company I=E2=80=99ve mentioned a few times=
 over the past couple years, Farcaster.=20
Farcaster is a crypto company, a decentralized social network, but I want y=
ou to try to not think about it with any of the baggage you might associate=
 with crypto as you read this piece. Think about it as a platform or a netw=
ork.=20
In Chris Dixon=E2=80=99s new book, Read Write Own [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/1c6df092-2b02-4afd-bf34-263234384edd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], which comes out today, he uses the t=
erm =E2=80=9Cblockchain network=E2=80=9D as an alternative to corporate net=
works like Facebook and Twitter and protocols networks like SMTP and HTTP. =
=E2=80=9CBlockchains are the only credible, known architecture,=E2=80=9D he=
 writes, =E2=80=9Cfor building networks with the societal benefits of proto=
col networks and the competitive advantages of corporate networks.=E2=80=9D=
 Farcaster is a blockchain network.
The benefits of blockchain networks can be hard to grok in the abstract. Wh=
at=E2=80=99s happening at Farcaster is a concrete and approachable example =
of why they might win, playing out in real time.
To see it for yourself, join Farcaster [ https://substack.com/redirect/c7e4=
c275-76b1-4668-9855-381691ac00a8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZj=
mlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. Cast me a hello when you=E2=80=99re there @pack=
y and share a link to this essay, and I=E2=80=99ll recast it to welcome you=
=2E=C2=A0
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.=C2=A0
Framing the Future of the Internet
Farcaster=E2=80=99s Very Small Apps Are a Very Big Deal
The god of the internet has a sense of humor, or at least a sense of timing=
=2E=C2=A0
In the same week that Apple proved that regulators can=E2=80=99t stop its A=
pp Store monopoly with its frustrating response [ https://substack.com/redi=
rect/b605d560-2638-49fe-ac65-f0f4ed652977?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA=
_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] to the EU=E2=80=99s Digital Markets Act=
 (DMA), Farcaster [ https://substack.com/redirect/c7e4c275-76b1-4668-9855-3=
81691ac00a8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU ] released Frames.=C2=A0
The connection between Apple=E2=80=99s App Store monopoly and Farcaster=E2=
=80=99s Frames might not be immediately obvious =E2=80=93 it might turn out=
 not to exist at all =E2=80=93 but Frames is the most compelling example of=
 why blockchain networks might ultimately disrupt corporate networks I=E2=
=80=99ve come across. It puts a bunch of ideas I=E2=80=99ve been writing ab=
out into production.=C2=A0
Let me take a step back, though. Starting with a couple questions you might=
 be asking: what is Farcaster and what are Frames?=C2=A0
Farcaster is a sufficiently decentralized social network [ https://substack=
=2Ecom/redirect/b7d22956-a297-41fa-9cc=
e-57a2409326bb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.g=
b8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] founded by Dan Romero and Varu=
n Srinivasan.=C2=A0
Farcaster is a protocol, responsible for storing things like user=E2=80=99s=
 handles, casts (Farcaster=E2=80=99s version of tweets), and reactions (lik=
e likes and recasts).=C2=A0
Anyone can build their own clients on top of Farcaster that use that data b=
ut offer different frontend experiences.=C2=A0
Clients are interfaces through which users access the feed. We don=E2=80=99=
t use that word =E2=80=9Cclient=E2=80=9D much anymore, because in most mode=
rn social networks, like Twitter and Facebook, the protocol and the client =
are the same thing. Twitter used to have clients, like Tweetdeck and Twitte=
rific, until it shut down its API access and killed the clients. Now, Twitt=
er is just Twitter (or, if you prefer, X).=C2=A0
You can think of Farcaster as a Twitter that=E2=80=99s extensible by its co=
mmunity and always will be.=C2=A0
The Farcaster team built its own client, Warpcast [ https://substack.com/re=
