ng about:
Small Applications, Growing Protocols
From Experimentation to Infrastructure
Why Blockchain Networks Win=C2=A0
I=E2=80=99ll cover each in turn.=C2=A0
Small Applications, Growing Protocols=C2=A0
In Small Applications, Growing Protocols [ https://substack.com/redirect/53=
b4bb2a-59b4-4697-b7f3-50d00eebef8e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaM=
ZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], I wrote about the fact that apps are getting =
easier to build and harder to sustain. Companies like Lensa, Poparazzi, BeR=
eal, Dispo, and Clubhouse gained millions of users, and even made millions =
of dollars, before fading away.=C2=A0
Variant=E2=80=99s Li Jin made a similar point in a recent essay [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/58cd945d-e359-44d3-bd6f-1745ff64b831?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], =E2=80=9CIn a sense, c=
onsumer products now resemble entertainment, with users regularly wanting t=
o try out the latest thing and then quickly moving on.=E2=80=9D
So what to do? I proposed a third path beyond raising money or bootstrappin=
g:
Small Apps that recognize their fleeting nature can team up with protocols =
that are built to last to build something bigger and more durable collectiv=
ely.
Turns out, I wasn=E2=80=99t thinking small enough. Frames are very small ap=
ps, some meant to be as fleeting as a tweet, others to serve as portals to =
larger apps, like Sound or Paragraph.=C2=A0
Developers and creators gain distribution, and the Farcaster protocol gains=
