Crypto=E2=80=99s UX has been famously terrible (although it=E2=80=99s impro=
ving). With Frames, users can go to one feed instead of a hundred different=
 apps to do the various things they might want to do.
That=E2=80=99s good for the developers and creators, because it means one p=
lace to reach thousands (and maybe someday millions) of users and frictionl=
ess conversion.=C2=A0
Li=E2=80=99s partner at Variant Jesse Walden calls Frames a new go-to-marke=
t strategy, writing [ https://substack.com/redirect/7bd2d152-a9f2-493a-876c=
-48b282dbb66c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Ex=
kRNpU ]:
For founders, the takeaway is that you now have the ability to tap directly=
 into existing user attention, engagement, identity and data as you plan yo=
ur GTM, the same way that Zynga famously did with Facebook. Only this time,=
