ery.
The only way out of that competition is differentiation; granted, Walmart h=
as tried buying and launching new brands exclusive to its store, but differ=
entiation when it comes to e-commerce goods doesn=E2=80=99t arise from top =
down planning. Rather, it bubbles up from widespread opportunity (and churn=
!), like that created by Shopify, supported by an entire aligned ecosystem.
You can find and replace =E2=80=9CAmazon=E2=80=9D with =E2=80=9CTwitter,=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=9CWalmart=E2=80=9D with =E2=80=9CThreads,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=
=9CShopify=E2=80=9D with =E2=80=9CFarcaster=E2=80=9D and the argument works=
 just as well.=C2=A0
(I=E2=80=99m not trying to make the ecommerce analogy directly, but interes=
tingly, Alex Danco, who works on making Shopify wallet aware [ https://subs=
tack.com/redirect/9196c2c8-5969-4aba-bf3c-6589c53402c0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], tweeted [ https://substac=
k.com/redirect/2d3efb8b-9d7e-4a4c-a467-28b19b9e0335?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.=
gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]: =E2=80=9Cframes are a key mi=
ssing piece of ecommerce infra that now suddenly works.=E2=80=9D This thing=
 has levels.)
By enabling widespread opportunity and encouraging competition (for attenti=
on) and churn at the experimentation layer, and building an aligned ecosyst=
em of developers who benefit from a larger and more engaged community of us=
ers, Farcaster has the opportunity to build differentiated social infrastru=
cture and succeed where other Twitter competitors have failed.=C2=A0
Why Blockchain Networks Win
Building new infrastructure bottoms-up is a slow, messy, winding process. I=
t looks like the experimentation layer until it becomes part of the infrast=
ructure layer.=C2=A0
There are all of these attributes of blockchain networks that people in cry=
pto like to talk about, things like decentralization, composability, and pe=
rmissionlessness. I like to write about those things, too, but I get that t=
hey can seem a little abstract.=C2=A0
A bet that blockchain networks will win is a bet that these attributes will=
, over time, allow richer ecosystems to develop on top of them.=C2=A0
One of the reasons you might want those attributes is to prevent bad things=
 from happening.=C2=A0
When Twitter killed Substack links back in April of last year, I wrote a pi=
ece called Crypto (Could) Fixes This [ https://substack.com/redirect/74b630=
4d-b458-4c8e-a1bb-2b7bc79d19de?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjml=
XXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] about how sufficiently decentralized social networ=
ks [ https://substack.com/redirect/b7d22956-a297-41fa-9cce-57a2409326bb?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] like Fa=
rcaster could prevent things like that from happening.=C2=A0
A sufficiently decentralized protocol, on the other hand, would need the ma=
jority of its token holders to wake up feeling petty in order to do the sam=
e thing, or even more if big changes required some sort of supermajority.
Defense wins championships, but defense is also boring. It=E2=80=99s hard t=
o attract a lot of users to a new product with a =E2=80=9Cjust-in-case=E2=
=80=9D value proposition.=C2=A0
Another reason you might want those things is to enable more good things to=
 happen.
That=E2=80=99s how great products that millions of people use get built: by=
 creating differentiated experiences that people love.=C2=A0
Frames is a tangible example of that kind of decentralization, composabilit=
y, and permissionlessness in action.=C2=A0
Decentralization: Builders can build on Farcaster knowing they won=E2=80=99=
t be rugged.
Composability: Developers can snap their Lego blocks into Farcaster=E2=80=
=99s infrastructure and other developers=E2=80=99 Lego blocks, to experimen=
t without needing to build the full stack or find new users. Wallets are bu=
ilt in, facilitating commerce and gating.=C2=A0As people build new things, =
everyone can remix them.
Permissionless: Anyone can create Frames, and Frames work in any Farcaster =
client, not just Warpcast.=C2=A0
More succinctly, Frames allow anyone, anywhere to easily build small apps w=
ith capabilities that grow as other people build new things, with the knowl=
edge that the platform can=E2=80=99t change the rules on them.
We=E2=80=99re just starting to see what=E2=80=99s possible, even if early e=
xperiments look like toys. I expect that in the coming weeks and months, pe=
ople will build easy ways to send payments, sell tickets, and do all sorts =
of things that happen a few clicks away from the feed on Twitter.=C2=A0
One possible use case that I=E2=80=99m particularly excited by are predicti=
on markets Frames, one of the ideas I=E2=80=99ve seen mentioned most since =
the launch.=C2=A0
Instead of simply firing off random predictions, the prediction markets Fra=
me might let people express their conviction by putting their money where t=
heir mouth is. Casting pessimistic predictions is easy; it would be great f=
or humanity if it were a little more expensive. With prediction frames, I s=
uspect that there would be a lot of signal in what currently amounts to a l=
ot of noise.=C2=A0
Live sports betting makes a lot of sense, too. Farcaster already has channe=
ls for the major sports leagues and teams. Adding betting in those channels=
 would make Farcaster the social place to gather around live sports. (Obvio=
usly, rules vary by jurisdiction.)
0xdesigner highlighted another killer use case: Instant Checkout.=C2=A0
That one is compelling because it removes friction from commerce (onchains =
capitalism [ https://substack.com/redirect/86cd64ad-3da2-4226-b20f-98fab243=
4eba?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]) =
in a way that one-click checkout companies could only dream of (they don=E2=
=80=99t have their own social feeds) and enables attribution in a way that =
marketers dream of. If I share a product in a Frame and you buy it, it=E2=
=80=99s clear that I=E2=80=99m the one who got you to buy it. The brand can=
 send affiliate revenue right into my wallet, no tracking link required. An=
d it will only be possible thanks to composability: as developers build zer=
o-knowledge tools that allow me to store my personal information and addres=
s in a wallet without exposing them to the world, anyone building an Instan=
t Checkout Frame can plug them in permissionlessly.=C2=A0
