></table></figure></div><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Turns out, I wasn&#8217;t t=
hinking small enough. Frames are </span><em>very</em><span> small apps, som=
e meant to be as fleeting as a tweet, others to serve as portals to larger =
apps, like Sound or Paragraph.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Developers=
 and creators gain distribution, and the Farcaster protocol gains activity =
and users.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Crypto&#8217;s UX has been famously t=
errible (although it&#8217;s improving). With Frames, users can go to one f=
eed instead of a hundred different apps to do the various things they might=
 want to do.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That&#8217;s good for the developers and =
creators, because it means one place to reach thousands (and maybe someday =
millions) of users and frictionless conversion.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
<span>Li&#8217;s partner at Variant Jesse Walden calls Frames a new go-to-m=
arket strategy, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/7bd2d152-a9=
f2-493a-876c-48b282dbb66c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: un=
derline;">writing</a><span>:</span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4p=
x solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64=
, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left:=
 20px;"><em><span>For founders, the takeaway is that you now have the abili=
ty to tap directly into existing user attention, engagement, identity and d=
ata as you plan your GTM, the same way that Zynga famously did with Faceboo=
k. Only this time, users&#8217; money will be there too, and their identity=
 and data </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/6ab1a7b0-c8ad-466=
0-a274-41002e7abc63?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underlin=
e;">can&#8217;t be rugged from underneath you</a><span>.&#160;&#160;</span>=
</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">And it&#8217;s good for Farcaster, =
because it means that thousands of developers and creators will be working =
to build experiences that attract activities and users, and that the Farcas=
ter protocol has a shot at becoming the center of gravity for onchain activ=
ity.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Thousands of small apps (Frames) working to=
 grow one protocol (Farcaster).&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-wi=
dget" style=3D"-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing=
: antialiased; -webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility; -webkit-font-smoothi=
ng: antialiased; appearance: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fo=
nt-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helveti=
ca, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Sym=
bol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1=
em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>From Experimentation to Infras=
tructure</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The relationship between apps=
 and protocols is a specific example of a more general relationship I&#8217=
;ve been thinking about a lot recently: </span><strong>experimentation </st=
rong><span>and </span><strong>infrastructure.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;"><span>Good infrastructure enables </span><strong>experimentation</st=
rong><span>; experimentation solidifies </span><strong>infrastructure</stro=
ng><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In </span><em><a href=3D"https=
://substack.com/redirect/7af12a9d-9151-496d-bdcb-bf788858581a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: =
rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Pace Layers</a><span>, </span=
></em><span>I wrote that &#8220;Strong infrastructure and good governance p=
rovide freedom through constraint.&#8221; Stable infrastructure provides a =
base for experimentation: the stronger and more stable the infrastructure, =
the easier it is to experiment on top of it.&#160;&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">By making it incredibly easy to experiment, and by guaranteeing t=
hat users&#8217; &#8220;identity and data can&#8217;t be rugged from undern=
eath you,&#8221; Farcaster encourages more experimentation.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">The relationship works the other way, too. The more experimenta=
tion there is at the top layer, the more stable the infrastructure below it=
 becomes.&#160;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">One way to visualize the role of=
 platforms in the context of Pace Layers is by thinking of experiments &#82=
11; or apps &#8211; as weights. The more experiments run on top of a platfo=
rm, the deeper into the layers the platform sinks and the more firmly it&#8=
217;s held in place.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-stati=
