16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There are all of these attrib=
utes of blockchain networks that people in crypto like to talk about, thing=
s like decentralization, composability, and permissionlessness. I like to w=
rite about those things, too, but I get that they can seem a little abstrac=
t.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">A bet that blockchain networks will win is a =
bet that these attributes will, over time, allow richer ecosystems to devel=
op on top of them.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>One of the reasons you =
might want those attributes is to </span><strong>prevent bad things from ha=
ppening</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>When Twitte=
r killed Substack links back in April of last year, I wrote a piece called =
</span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/74b6304d-b458-4c8e-a1bb=
-2b7bc79d19de?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Ex=
kRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Cr=
ypto (Could) Fixes This</a></em><span> about how </span><a href=3D"https://=
substack.com/redirect/b7d22956-a297-41fa-9cce-57a2409326bb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">sufficiently decentralized socia=
l networks</a><span> like Farcaster could prevent things like that from hap=
pening.&#160;</span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9=
; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>A s=
ufficiently decentralized protocol, on the other hand, would need the major=
ity of its token holders to wake up feeling petty in order to do the same t=
hing, or even more if big changes required some sort of supermajority.</em>=
</p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Defense wins championships, but defense =
is also boring. It&#8217;s hard to attract a lot of users to a new product =
with a &#8220;just-in-case&#8221; value proposition.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;"><span>Another reason you might want those things is to </span><strong>=
enable more good things to happen</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">That&#8217;s how great products that millions of people use get built: b=
y creating differentiated experiences that people love.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Frames is a tangible example of that kind of decentralization, co=
mposability, and permissionlessness in action.&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margin=
-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format=
: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: =
4px;"><strong>Decentralization:</strong><span> Builders can build on Farcas=
ter knowing they won&#8217;t be rugged.</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin:=
 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-=
box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;=
 margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Composability: </strong><spa=
n>Developers can snap their Lego blocks into Farcaster&#8217;s infrastructu=
re and other developers&#8217; Lego blocks, to experiment without needing t=
o build the full stack or find new users. Wallets are built in, facilitatin=
g commerce and gating.&#160;As people build new things, everyone can remix =
them.</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format:=
 bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4=
px;"><strong>Permissionless: </strong><span>Anyone can create Frames, and F=
rames work in any Farcaster client, not just Warpcast.&#160;</span></p></li=
></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>More succinctly, </span><strong>Frames allow =
anyone, anywhere to easily build small apps with capabilities that grow as =
</strong><em><strong>other</strong></em><strong> people build new things, w=
ith the knowledge that the platform can&#8217;t change the rules on them.</=
strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We&#8217;re just starting to see what&#8217;s =
possible, even if early experiments look like toys. I expect that in the co=
ming weeks and months, people will build easy ways to send payments, sell t=
ickets, and do all sorts of things that happen a few clicks away from the f=
eed on Twitter.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>One possible use case that=
 I&#8217;m particularly excited by are </span><strong>prediction markets Fr=
ames</strong><span>, one of the ideas I&#8217;ve seen mentioned most since =
the launch.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Instead of simply firing off =
random predictions, the prediction markets Frame might let people express t=
heir conviction by putting their money where their mouth is. Casting pessim=
istic predictions is easy; it would be great for humanity if it were a litt=
le more expensive. With prediction frames, I suspect that there would be a =
lot of signal in what currently amounts to a lot of noise.&#160;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;"><strong>Live sports betting</strong><span> makes a lot of sense,=
 too. Farcaster already has channels for the major sports leagues and teams=
=2E Adding betting in those channels wo=
uld make Farcaster the social place to=
 gather around live sports. (Obviously, rules vary by jurisdiction.)</span>=
